5
6
</pre></td><td class="rouge-code"><pre>---
slug: cool-stuff
name: Cool Stuff
description: &gt;
             This is an awesome description of my cool stuff tag which will be display underneath the title of this tag's page.
---
</pre></td></tr></tbody></table></code></pre></div></div>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">slug</code> is a mandatory field and defines tagâ€™s slug, accessible at <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">yourblog.com/tag/dactl/</code>, use <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">-</code> instead of spaces here.<br />
<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">name</code> is a mandatory field and defines tagâ€™s name, e.g. <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Cool Stuff</code>.<br />
<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">description</code> is an optional field, itâ€™s visible on tagâ€™s page.<br />
Click <a href="/tag/dactl">here</a> and <a href="/tag/howto">here</a> to see the difference.</p>

